narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Italian 1 starts out very intense - it is a surprise to be put in a class in which you are being taught in the language you are trying to learn - but you will catch on. I learned as much Italian in one semester as French in 5 years of middle/high school study.
YES!! So much fun. Awesome. Take it!! Italian is such a great language to learn!

I would recommend Italian 110 07 to another student. After one semester, I feel that I could communicate, read, and write reasonably well in Italian and have a basic understanding of the language and its grammar.
Yes. Take this language. The language is beautiful, the TAs are great, and thethe language isn't terribly hard to learn. Do it.
I would definitely recommend it. You feel so accomplished when you get to the end of the semester and can actually hold a conversation in Italian.
